\dfrac{x}{x+1}\;\;
\;\;1 - \dfrac{1}{x+1}
\frac{x}{x+1}=\frac{x+1-1}{x+1}=\frac{x+1}{x+1}-\frac{1}{x+1}=1-\frac{1}{x+1}
\dfrac{17}{20}
\dfrac{17}{20} = \dfrac{20 - 3}{20} = \dfrac{20}{20} - \dfrac{3}{20}
\dfrac{x}{x+1}
\dfrac{x}{(x+1)}\; = \;\dfrac{(x+1) - 1}{(x+1)} \;=\; \dfrac{(x+1)}{(x+1)} - \dfrac{1}{(x+1)} \;=\; 1 - \dfrac{1}{(x+1)}
1
-1
\dfrac{x}{x+1} = 1 - \dfrac{1}{x+1}
1 - \frac{1}{x+1}
1 - \frac{1}{x+1} = \frac{x+1}{x+1} - \frac{1}{x+1} = \frac{x}{x+1}
